				<table width="100%" cellspacing="5">
				<tr>
					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">I could never really get into trackers so I'm more for MML. I'm no musician but I can read sheet music, and MML is basically like writing sheet music but with symbols easily typed on a PC keyboard rather than stripes and tadpoles.<br /><br />One problem with MML is that there is no Famitone for it. PPMCK is feature-rich but it seems to be mainly for making NSFs rather than homebrew development, and also you are restricted to NESASM. NSDL seems good but with that you are restricted to CC65/CA65.<br /><br />In the end I decided it was a good idea to learn how to make my own sound engine, and it was very worthwhile. It shouldn't be too hard to make an MML interpreter for it.</div>

					<br clear="all" /><br />

